text: Nate McConnell is a Democratic member of the Montana State Senate. He was previously part of the Montana House of Representatives, representing House District 89. He was first elected in 2014 and was reelected in 2016. ==Early life, education, and career== McConnell earned his J.D. from Southern Illinois University and became a sole practitioner in Missoula, Montana. ==Montana House of Representatives== In the 2014 primary, he defeated two fellow Democrats and faced no Republican opposition. In 2016, he defeated Republican Alex Krigsvold.
